<div id="review_2702652490" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2702652490" />
    <a title="Ioana Ioana" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/63497622-ioana-ioana"><img alt="Ioana Ioana" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1590230014p2/63497622.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2702652490?book_show_action=true">Apr 30, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ioana Ioana" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ioana Ioana" href="/user/show/63497622-ioana-ioana">Ioana Ioana</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/63497622-ioana-ioana?shelf=the-l-word">the-l-word</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/63497622-ioana-ioana?shelf=luminary">luminary</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/63497622-ioana-ioana?shelf=history-medieval">history-medieval</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2702652490" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14357200026609499963"><b>Undying...love?!? </b><br/><br/><br/>Who’d knew that Micromegas would ever mistake the Academy of Sciences with the Academy of Lagado.<br/><br/><br/>Who’d knew that a 12th century abbot who suffered trials and courted death could be so great a Man? What could explain the emergence of a mind set afire by its thirst for knowledge, out of the seemingly bottomless pit of an age so Dark? A bona fide <i>primus inter pares</i>. <br/><br/><br/>Words fail to do justice to the best book I’ve ever read.<br/><br/><br/><br/>——————————————————————<br/><br/><i>”You are buried inside my breast for </i></span>
  <span id="freeText14357200026609499963" style="display:none"><b>Undying...love?!? </b><br /><br /><br />Who’d knew that Micromegas would ever mistake the Academy of Sciences with the Academy of Lagado.<br /><br /><br />Who’d knew that a 12th century abbot who suffered trials and courted death could be so great a Man? What could explain the emergence of a mind set afire by its thirst for knowledge, out of the seemingly bottomless pit of an age so Dark? A bona fide <i>primus inter pares</i>. <br /><br /><br />Words fail to do justice to the best book I’ve ever read.<br /><br /><br /><br />——————————————————————<br /><br /><i>”You are buried inside my breast for eternity, from which tomb you will never emerge as long as I live. There you lie, there you rest. You keep me company right until I fall asleep; while I sleep you never leave me, and after I wake I see you, as soon as I open my eyes, even before the light of day itself. To others I address my words, to you my intention. I often stumble over words, because my thought is far from them. Who then will be able to deny that you are truly buried in me?”</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="14357200026609499963" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


