  <span id="freeText9215864254162481803" style="display:none">I loved this book when I read it the first time back in the 90s, still do today.<br /><br />What baffles me are all the incompetent and unsympathetic reviews that love to bash Abelard. Apparently the don't get what goes on with the male mind after the male in question has been <em>castrated</em> against his will. That's bound to leave physical and emotional scarring!</span>
